column2: Displayed are Enterococcus bacteria counts.  The maximum daily limit is 104 counts/100 mL.
A swimming advisory is declared by the DCR for the following day if counts exceed 104
counts/100 mL or if the 5-day running geometric mean exceeds 35 counts/100 mL
Daily rainfall totals from Logan Airport, National Weather Service raingauge
All results are in counts/100 mL and testing is performed by DCR and MWRA.
2007 beach monitoring was conducted daily beginning June 18, and ended August 31.
A swimming advisory is posted due to either high Enterococcus counts or rainfall.
